```python
def longest_word(words):
    if not words:
        return None
    return max(words, key=len)

words = {'this', 'is', 'a', 'test'}
print(longest_word(words))
```

However, this code will return only one of the longest words if there are multiple words with the same maximum length. To find all the longest words, you can modify the code as follows:

```python
def longest_words(words):
    if not words:
        return None
    max_length = max(len(word) for word in words)
    return [word for word in words if len(word) == max_length]

words = {'this', 'is', 'a', 'test'}
print(longest_words(words))
```

This code will return a list of all the longest words in the set. In this case, it will return `['this', 'test']`.

